rmalization, but maintain stop-loss levels to manage downside risk.  \n• Use of Hedging Tools: To mitigate volatility, incorporate options strategies (like protective puts) or allocate a portion of your portfolio to lower beta assets (such as utilities or defensive ETFs).  \n• Diversify Fixed Income Exposure: With treasury yields adjusting, explore a mix of short-to-intermediate bonds to cushion against further rate adjustments while remaining flexible to rebalance as conditions evolve.\n\nOverall, a balanced, diversified approach that emphasizes quality and risk management should help navigate the current market uncertainties."
